topic.title: Port Arbitration Command

body.p: Switchtec supports two types of Port Arbitration Modes:
In Weighted Round Robin (WRR) mode, the arbitration initial count for all ports needs to be specified.
The MRPC Port Arbitration Command can be used to set or get the port arbitration mode and initial count in WRR mode.

row.entry: Input Physical Port ID is invalid

section.p: This field specifies the sub-command ID.

row.entry: Get Port Arbitration Mode and the WRR arbitration initial count. If the current Port Arbitration Mode is in FRR, this command will still read all the WRR arbitration initial count registers and fill them in the return data buffer.
Set Port Arbitration Mode and the WRR arbitration initial count for WRR mode. If the Port Arbitration Mode is set to FRR, then the WRR arbitration initial count fields will be ignored.

section.p: This field indicates the physical port number where only physical ports 0-47 are allowed to configure the port arbitration mode.
This field indicates the port arbitration mode to set.
These fields indicates the WRR Arbitration Initial Count for all ports in WRR mode. The ports 48 to 55 go to the Switchtec PCIe Processing Unit (PPU) Channels.
